text.tspan: field far beyond form and emptiness
Beings are numberless, I vow to save them.
Delusions are inexhaustible, I vow to end them,
Dharma gates are endless, I vow to enter them,
Buddha’s way is unsurpassable, I vow to become it
May the good that comes from
and touch all that live there.
To all Buddhas in ten directions, past present and future
to all the bodhisatvas and patriarchs,
when practicing deeply the Prajna Paramita,
perceived that all five skandhas are empty
and was saved from all suffering and distress.
“Shariputra, form does not differ from emptiness;
emptiness does not differ from form.
That which is form is emptiness,
The same is true of feelings,
Shariputra, all dharmas are marked with emptiness;
they do not appear nor disappear,
no eyes, no ears, no nose,
no tongue, no body, no mind;
no color, no sound, no smell,
no taste, no touch, no object of mind;
no realm of eyes and so forth
no ignorance and also no extinction of it,
and also no extinction of them;
Without any hindrance no fears exist;
far apart from every perverted view,
In the three worlds all Buddhas depend on
which is able to relieve all suffering
So proclaim the Prajna Paramita mantra,
